<subSubSection id="9C6060A89F5230EC5582FE0E044DAF7B" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="010EB86559BE34868E6755B2E8A7ABDE" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="950073C8EE79802E9593CDFDF279FCF3" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
Based on the descriptions of 
<bibRefCitation id="D1A8D7A644ED6A4AC4B9A6EEA61FC954" author="Solovyev, AV" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" refId="B19" refString="Solovyev, AV, Witt, ThJ, 2009. The Limacodidae of Vietnam. Entomofauna (Supplement No. 16): 33-229." title="The Limacodidae of Vietnam. Entomofauna (Supplement No. 16): 33 - 229." year="2009">Solovyev and Witt (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6E10D3C5EE4E6D1AC04E3A2E34267DB8" genus="M." lsidName="M. aerata" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="aerata">
<emphasis id="8420154C073501B83DFAAC513CA1DDFE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">M. aerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extremely similar in appearance to its rare Himalayan congener 
<taxonomicName id="0E72CCBBF850BDDC9C1DCB32DE70506F" genus="M." lsidName="M. cuprea" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="cuprea">
<emphasis id="82262941C10FE9909CCB94FDD10D5A17" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">M. cuprea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Moore, 1879). The difference between them is that the former has a better-defined border of the distal pale zone in the forewings, whereas the same area in 
<taxonomicName id="4DF76BDF5AFE3770F72DECA11D29CF68" genus="M." lsidName="M. cuprea" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="cuprea">
<emphasis id="49722BFCE6814CD5384C81A871252BD8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">M. cuprea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is smooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6B4A1EDB22FCE5E24D1BD294A414510F" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="bionomics">
<paragraph id="804A3806C338F0ED504444488E28C969" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Bionomics.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6ABB8BD3E8EB69232EA3E39DC8D4BE0B" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
The specimens were collected from May to June at altitudes of ~ 850 m a.s.l. The collection area is a subtropical climate zone (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D6018EE7B0D1E5A66709F5BF097A1A6C" captionStart="Figures 24–27" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 24 - 27. Biotopes: 24 China, Chongqing Municipality, Mt. Simian, biotope of Iragoides elongata Hering, 1931, photo by J. Wu 25 - 27 China, SE Xizang, Linzhi City, Motuo County: 25 Beibeng Countryside, Dergong Village, biotope of Iragoides peiwangi sp. nov., Caelestomorpha serratus sp. nov., Euphlyctina phaeopasta (Hampson, 1906) and Mummu aerata Solovyev &amp; Witt, 2009, photo by H. L. Han 26, 27 two different collecting sites in Gedang Countryside, biotope of Caelestomorpha serratus sp. nov. and Euphlyctina phaeopasta (Hampson, 1906), photo by J. Wu." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1100.76142.figures24-27" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/683243" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">25</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="FF25D6C157745DEA6DDDE7F4B48E9D42" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1100.76142.figures24-27" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/683243" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" start="Figures 24–27" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="9B24685D5F75CBD9EE222B873D7026B6" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="A426A62FD5CAE606238DE005EE620C79" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Figures 24-27.</emphasis>
Biotopes: 
<emphasis id="3ACC7659C5567C7F9E56C443FC495DFE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">24</emphasis>
China, Chongqing Municipality, Mt. Simian, biotope of 
<taxonomicName id="016E31D548B4718A4567209266D7437C" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Iragoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iragoides elongata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="8B81EC612F16A6698D9895A4A30FCF57" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Iragoides elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hering, 1931, photo by J. Wu 
<emphasis id="E3D5C95C7CED8E9C2F00964863D3167A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">25-27</emphasis>
China, SE Xizang, Linzhi City, Motuo County: 
<emphasis id="AB5DE1B2C4710E82AB89C245ADE674FA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">25</emphasis>
Beibeng Countryside, Dergong Village, biotope of 
<taxonomicName id="B58CF1292D7CF95CFF1709FEDA7D39F4" authorityName="Wu &amp; Solovyev &amp; Han" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Iragoides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iragoides peiwangi" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peiwangi">
<emphasis id="993F841A4564E6CD228291E6AB383BC6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Iragoides peiwangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., 
<taxonomicName id="BF5FB4DA75EAB68A515BE0A53AECFA60" authorityName="Wu &amp; Solovyev &amp; Han" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Caelestomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Caelestomorpha serratus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serratus">
<emphasis id="136F4603855D5FBD2B3808763E3C13DD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Caelestomorpha serratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., 
<taxonomicName id="FB5A1B8A11B1AD8E0A4D13F2940304DA" authorityName=", new species record for China" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Euphlyctina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euphlyctina phaeopasta" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phaeopasta">
<emphasis id="D0806389ABAD568C2904ECA2C5660871" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Euphlyctina phaeopasta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hampson, 1906) and 
<taxonomicName id="9D4A4ABCAEBC88A158CABB465E3D4DBF" authorityName="Solovyev &amp; Witt" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Mummu" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mummu aerata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aerata">
<emphasis id="C570278B2C5483E3F8BEBAB267749711" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Mummu aerata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Solovyev &amp; Witt, 2009, photo by H.L. Han 
<emphasis id="8C08ECE56D3D8A323CF311DB0D435886" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">26, 27</emphasis>
two different collecting sites in Gedang Countryside, biotope of 
<taxonomicName id="1A76FCAA633BDC64E8BED7ECEF5444A9" authorityName="Wu &amp; Solovyev &amp; Han" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Caelestomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Caelestomorpha serratus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serratus">
<emphasis id="384953A670951A9F4372618F8EB226A8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Caelestomorpha serratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. and 
<taxonomicName id="D4BACEB1A2C1DF34A1D0E80B7E3BE673" authorityName=", new species record for China" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Euphlyctina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euphlyctina phaeopasta" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phaeopasta">
<emphasis id="F858492AE7D3268D9A6440DE53AAB496" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Euphlyctina phaeopasta</emphasis>
