<subSubSection id="550ADAD4AA8CB428F2035307822BC318" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8583A878BB92B0FD64AE43F4BD085BE3" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0EF77B1B14C667F683AB46209B1EF73C" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">China (Xizang: Motuo; Yunnan: Lancang), Thailand, Vietnam.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="855F6BA5A34427039C695E4F9F770650" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="BD1DF4CD0DCC716826BAB737348F747A" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C78C71583CFDA9FAFF966171B09F4B4D" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
The genus is associated with the genera 
<taxonomicName id="7B81CD1BCB3C8031D6300FCF53A65272" authorityName="Holloway" authorityYear="1986" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Pseudonirmides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudonirmides" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6F98DC179D8B237AF4B5D0C4904A3EF2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Pseudonirmides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Holloway, 1986, 
<taxonomicName id="91ED2E11ABCB172D6C5D16290CCFE14E" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Nirmides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nirmides" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4737349167963DFC928912F91547BBF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Nirmides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hering, 1931 and 
<taxonomicName id="54990A204F57DC97EC6727950BBE1A64" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Chibiraga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chibiraga" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="132784560469163BD6BC61BDF76E26A4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Chibiraga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Matsumura, 1931 both in appearance and the smaller pairwise distances of 
<emphasis id="CB8A189E0A48A76DD98F0B10EDDAC76C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">COI</emphasis>
(0.097-0.137) (
<bibRefCitation id="593FE72A4F98BCD592CAD99AD85C651E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1163/1876312X-45012111" author="Solovyev, AV" journalOrPublisher="Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 36" refId="B14" refString="Solovyev, AV, 2015. Morphological and taxonomical review of the genus Nirmides Hering (Lepidoptera, Limacodidae) with description of eight new species. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution 46 (1): 1 - 36, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1163/1876312X-45012111" title="Morphological and taxonomical review of the genus Nirmides Hering (Lepidoptera, Limacodidae) with description of eight new species." url="https://doi.org/10.1163/1876312X-45012111" volume="46" year="2015">Solovyev 2015</bibRefCitation>
); however, the presence of the strongly modified asymmetric juxta with a large, finger-shaped, hairy right process and the absence of the saccular processes of valvae are the diagnostic features.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
